&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About Alpha Lion&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Alpha Lion is one of the fastest-growing performance nutrition brands in the US. We exist to help men over 30 reject age decline and dominate every decade. We deliver powerful, science-backed performance nutrition products that help men optimize their biology, maximize their potential, and build lasting vitality at every life stage.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Over 5,000,000 men have made our products part of their daily routine, and we’re scaling fast, building new categories, expanding channels, and investing in the capabilities that turn a fast-growing brand into a lasting one.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a rare opportunity to build a function from the ground up inside a company that’s scaling fast and taking it seriously.&amp;nbsp;You’ll be the first person in this role, reporting directly to the CMO, with a mandate to shape what products we build, who we build them for, and how we take them to market. You’ll own the Market &amp;amp; Consumer Insights Engine, the function that feeds every major product, growth, and go-to-market decision with validated intelligence.&amp;nbsp;This is hands-on intelligence work, not managing analysts. You’ll build and run the research infrastructure that doesn’t exist today and translate it into clear, digestible recommendations that the entire leadership team acts on.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a high-leverage, high-impact, highly visible role where your work directly determines the quality of every product and growth decision the company makes.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You’ll Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;margin: 0px; padding: 0px;&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Consumer &amp;amp; Market Research:&lt;/strong&gt; Run the primary research cadence: customer interviews, surveys, review mining, support log analysis, buyer persona tracking, NPS and satisfaction diagnostics to build a continuously updated picture of who our customer is and what’s changing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Competitive Intelligence:&lt;/strong&gt; Build and maintain the system that tracks how competitors position, price, formulate, and sell. Deliver competitor briefs at cadence and surface signals before they become threats.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Product Validation:&lt;/strong&gt; Provide TAM/SAM sizing, demand validation, positioning hypotheses, and pricing research as inputs to our stage gate process. Recommend No-Go when conviction is insufficient.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Diagnostics:&lt;/strong&gt; Identify what’s working and what’s broken. Synthesize churn drivers, product quality issues, and satisfaction gaps using customer data and market benchmarks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Trend Monitoring:&lt;/strong&gt; Track macro trends shaping our category: GLP-1 adoption, ingredient shifts, regulatory changes, media platform evolution, and consumer behavior changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Cross-Functional Delivery:&lt;/strong&gt; Translate insights into clear, digestible formats for Product, Growth, Retention, and Leadership. Provide creative and positioning recommendations to the Growth and Media teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Insights System:&lt;/strong&gt; Build the operating system from scratch: research standards, workflows, a centralized repository, and learning loops so this function scales beyond you.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
